Question -4
Write the follwing expression in a java program
v^2-u^2/2*a*s

public class PhysicsFormula {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        float a = 5f;
        float S = 6f;
        float v = 7f;
        float u = 8f;
        float x = (v * v) - (u * u);
        float y = (2 * a * S);
        float z = x / y;
        System.out.println("Result using steps: " + z);
        float result = (v * v - u * u) / (2 * a * S);
        
        System.out.println("Result using single line: " + result);
    }
}
Output:
Result using steps: -0.25
Result using single line: -0.25
